var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"Wei GENG","text":"Wei.Geng [AT] tum.de <p>I am a doctoral reseacher &amp; Ph.D. candidate supervised by Prof. Dr.-Ing. J\u00f6rg Ott at Chair of Connected Mobility, TUM, advised by Prof. Nitinder Mohan at TU Delft, mentored by Prof. Dirk Kutscher at HKUST(GZ). My current research interests lie in Accelerating Critical Applications by Edge Computing and AI.</p>"},{"location":"index.html#-short-bio","title":"\ud83d\udcc4 Short Bio","text":"<p>Before joining TUM, I obtained my M.Phil. degree from HKUST(GZ), where I was luckily advised by Prof. Pan Hui, Prof. Gareth Tyson, and Prof. Dirk Kutscher. Previously, I was a full-time R&amp;D Engineer focusing on systems performance optimization at Huawei and lucky to work with Mr. Jing Liu, Dr. Wei Wang, and Dr. Sui Zhou. I obtained my M.Eng and B.Eng from Fudan University and Harbin Engineering University in 2020 and 2017 respectively. I have internships in Alipay and eBay.</p>"},{"location":"index.html#-research-interests","title":"\ud83d\udcbb Research Interests","text":"<ul> <li>Edge Computing, Fog Computing<ul> <li>supporting critical applications latency-wise and efficiency-wise</li> <li>e.g., offload DL inference tasks from mobile/IoT devices to edge servers</li> </ul> </li> <li>Networked Systems<ul> <li>ML-enabled, e.g., ML-based task scheduling</li> <li>enabling-ML, e.g., distributed Inference</li> </ul> </li> <li>Programming Language Runtime and OS (not much anymore)<ul> <li>Golang runtime scheduler</li> <li>OS kernel optimization</li> </ul> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#-teaching--supervision","title":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\ud83c\udfeb Teaching &amp; Supervision","text":"<ul> <li>Summer Term 2025 - Seminar - Hot Topics in Edge Computing (IN2107, IN4417)</li> <li>Winter Term 2024/25 - Master Practical Course: Edge Computing and the IoT (IN2106, IN4261)</li> <li>Master/Bachelor Thesis Supervision - Please contact me if you are interested in working with me.</li> <li>Previous Teaching Assistant / Tutorals<ul> <li>Red Bird Challenge Camp @ HKUST(GZ)</li> <li>Python Programming @ Fudan University</li> </ul> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#-working-experience","title":"\ud83d\udcbc Working Experience","text":"<ul> <li> Huawei Technologies - Fulltime R&amp;D Software Engineer, Shanghai, 2020~2022.</li> <li> Ant Group - Intern, Hangzhou, Winter, 2019</li> <li> eBay - Intern, Shanghai, Summer, 2018</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#-education","title":"\ud83c\udf93 Education","text":"<ul> <li>Ph.D. Student - CIT,  Technical University of Munich, Munich, Germany - 2024.10~</li> <li>M.Phil. -  The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology, Guangzhou, China - 2022.9~2024.10</li> <li>M.Eng. -  Fudan University, Shanghai, China - 2017~2020</li> <li>B.Eng. -  Harbin Engineering University, Harbin, China - 2013~2017</li> <li>Visiting Student -  Politecnico di Milano, Milan, Italy - 2023.3</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#-hobbies","title":"\ud83c\udff8 Hobbies","text":"<ul> <li>Sports: Basketball, Badminton, Ping-pong.</li> <li>Chinese Hard Pen Calligraphy</li> <li>Reading Interests: History and Psychology</li> <li>Cooking: Zero-shot Cooking \ud83d\ude08</li> </ul>"},{"location":"news.html","title":"News","text":"News <p> 2024-3: Glad to visit Technische Universit\u00e4t Munich.  2024-2: Glad to visit Politecnico di Milano.  2023-09-04: Honored to be selected to receive an ACM Travel Grant and an RBM Research Travel Grant. 2023-08-16: Glad to become a reviewer for ACM ICN 2023 Poster and Demo Track. 2023-08-07: We got an accepted paper in ACM ICN 2023."}]}